cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.SI

This paper presents a deep learning framework using convolutional neural networks (CNN) and recurrent neural networks (RNN) for crop yield prediction based on environmental data and management practices. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as CNNs are commonly used in image analysis. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of LASSO, which is a popular method in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) and the backpropagation method, which is commonly used in neural networks and optimization (cs.SI).
